gpt-5.4 (openai-codex, tmux pi instance) audited the slot implementation
and found 3 bugs + 1 UX issue. All fixed with failing tests added first:

1. prime not slot-aggregated: checked only default ref, missed slot-only repos.
   Fixed: prime now uses _all_notes and _all_slot_refs for all sections.

2. compost --report ignored tree notes: only checked targets-path, not
   targets-treepath. Fixed: report now checks both path types.

3. git noise leak: _compost_note and _renew_note leaked 'Overwriting existing
   notes for object' from git notes add -f. Fixed: redirect stderr to /dev/null
   on internal git notes add calls. cmd_note keeps its own overwrite warning.

4. activate wildcard: codex flagged that git config notes.displayRef doesn't
   support wildcards for slot refs. Deferred — activate already iterates
   discovered refs via _all_slot_refs.

5 new audit tests added. 228 total, 0 failures.
